## SIMPLIFIED DATABASE SCHEMA

### Core Tables Only:
```sql
-- Groups (Simplified)
CREATE TABLE study_groups (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  creator_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  group_code VARCHAR(8) UNIQUE,
  is_public BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Group Members (Simplified)
CREATE TABLE group_members (
  group_id UUID REFERENCES study_groups(id),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  role VARCHAR(10) DEFAULT 'member', -- admin, member only
  joined_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (group_id, user_id)
);

-- Group Quiz Sessions (Core functionality)
CREATE TABLE group_quiz_sessions (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  group_id UUID REFERENCES study_groups(id),
  quiz_token VARCHAR(255),
  scheduled_at TIMESTAMP,
  created_by UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'scheduled', -- scheduled, active, completed
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Group Quiz Results (Essential for comparison)
CREATE TABLE group_quiz_results (
  session_id UUID REFERENCES group_quiz_sessions(id),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  score INTEGER,
  completed_at TIMESTAMP,
  result_data JSONB,
  PRIMARY KEY (session_id, user_id)
);

-- Simple Group Chat (Optional)
CREATE TABLE group_messages (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  group_id UUID REFERENCES study_groups(id),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users(id),
  content TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

## REALISTIC UI/UX FLOW

### Group Dashboard (Simplified):
```
Group Dashboard
├── Group Header (name, code, member count)
├── Quick Actions (Schedule Quiz, Invite Members)
├── Recent Quiz Sessions
├── Member List with Last Activity
├── Simple Group Stats
└── Group Chat (if implemented)
```

### Group Quiz Session Flow (Realistic):
1. **Pre-Session:** Teacher schedules session, members get notification
2. **Join Session:** Members join group quiz room, see who's online
3. **During Quiz:** All members take quiz simultaneously (no sync needed)
4. **Post-Quiz:** Group results comparison, simple celebration

